phase2.explanation:
You made everything `private` but forgot to provide public getters or setters!

**What's wrong:**
- No getters → can't read data
- No setters → can't modify data
- The class is useless

**The fix:**
```cpp
class Player {
private:
    std::string name;
    int health;

public:
    std::string getName() const { return name; }
    int getHealth() const { return health; }
    void setHealth(int h) { health = h; }
};
```

**PlusPlus-chan says:**
"Encapsulation is good. But don't lock everything away without a way to interact. Provide an interface!"

